Just as in the example in Fig. 5, this is only a third of the pixel rate
at a resolution of 1920√ó1080@60Hz (resulting in 1/ùëáùëù=148MHz),
meaning that each sample ùë¶[ùëô]will actually be a linear combination
of several tens of encoded bits, further complicating the image
