3 Results
For all results below, we call the fine-tuned model ‚ÄòFine-Tune‚Äô, the base model ‚ÄòBase‚Äô, and the fine-tuned
model with randomized labels the ‚ÄòControl‚Äô. We find substantial improvements in forecasting accuracy for
both Phi-4 14B and DeepSeek-R1 14B fine-tunes, heavily outperforming the ignorance benchmark of a Brier
score of 0.25 (arrived at by predicting 50% on every question) and improving upon the base and control
models (see Figure 5).
